news.title: Mumbai: EOW arrests Srinath Developer's director in cheating case
news.para: Interestingly, Ved is the same builder who was booked last week by the Tilak Nagar police for allegedly breaking into his flat which was sealed by the MahaRera officials for default payments.

news.title: IRDAI eases norms of bank bonds, InvITs/REITs
news.para: AT1 bonds have no fixed maturities and are raised to shore up the capital base. These quasi-equity securities yield much higher returns than traditional bonds as the risk is also larger.

news.title: Supertech twin towers' demolition possible on Aug 21 if 'charging' begins by Sunday
news.para: ‘Charging’, the term for packing explosives into the two towers, was supposed to begin on August 2, but deferred because the blast design and other aspects of the demolition are being scrutinised and vetted by the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI).

news.title: Yes Bank-DHFL scam: ED files 90-page chargesheet in special PMLA court
news.para: Earlier on Wednesday, ED attached assets totalling Rs 415 crore in Yes Bank- DHFL Fraud case. Of the total, Rs 251 crore assets were of Sanjay Chhabria and Rs 164 crore of Avinash Bhosale.

news.title: Income tax department searches office of Noida-based realtor
news.para: “We are verifying the links between the two firms (Broad and ACE). The officials have seized several documents, electronic gadgets and other material from the office,” the I-T source said.

news.title: Hindustan Construction Company posts net loss of Rs 280 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: HCC's total income during the quarter stood at Rs 2,242 crore compared to Rs 2,503.29 crore in the year-ago period. Its total expenses declined to Rs 2,497 crore from 2,579 crore a year earlier.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit rises 81% to Rs 254 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations rose 53.44 per cent to Rs 2,759.70 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 1,798.49 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Lodha Group acquires prime land parcel in Pune from Poonawalla Constructions
news.para: Macrotech Developers has acquired the land parcel along with a co-investor company Home Crest Constructions. The deal, for which Lodha has paid stamp duty worth Rs 5.60 crore, was concluded and registered on July 11, showed the documents accessed by ET.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit rises multi-fold to Rs 925.48 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: The housing financier is very positive about demand for housing loans going forward, he said. Net interest income (NII) rose 26 per cent to Rs 1,610.19 crore in the quarter against Rs 1,275.31 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: DLF mulls auction bid for Ambience Mall with base price of $366 million: Sources
news.para: The 1.2 million square feet "Ambience Mall" in the posh southern district of India's capital has been put up for auction as its current owner, the Ambience Group, has not paid debt of $149 million to Indiabulls Housing Finance and other creditors, according to a previously unreported public auction notice.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit down 26.8% at Rs 205 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations increased 27.44 per cent to Rs 3,302 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 2,591 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: CDPQ's arm sells Macrotech Developers' shares worth Rs 736 crore
news.para: ​Ivanhoe Op India Inc sold 43,84,464 shares on NSE and 26,44,464 shares on BSE, amounting to a 1.5 per cent stake in the company, as per the bulk deal data available with the National Stock Exchange (NSE) and BSE.

news.title: Indian rental housing searches grew 84.4% in Q2 2022: Magicbricks
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: SC seeks report on medical condition of ex-CMD of Amrapali Group
news.para: Advocate Manoj Singh, representing Sharma, said that the applicant is suffering from infection and his health "condition is deteriorating".

news.title: Income tax department raids Kanpur-based builder's house
news.para: The connection of Rakesh Yadav’s company with Ghanaram Infratech Company has come to the fore. The IT team is investigating the documents related to the company.
